1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,253
<i>What do you want? Why are you here?</i>

2
00:00:03,336 --> 00:00:05,255
<i>We just want to ask you about Kyle.</i>

3
00:00:07,215 --> 00:00:08,341
<i>Stop it!</i>

4
00:00:08,425 --> 00:00:09,926
- [gunshot]
<i>- Erica!</i>

5
00:00:10,010 --> 00:00:11,469
<i>- Marco!</i>
<i>- What are you doing here?!</i>

6
00:00:11,553 --> 00:00:13,388
[Kyle] <i>Don't fucking look at me.</i>

7
00:00:13,471 --> 00:00:14,639
- [Marco grunts]
- [blows land]

8
00:00:15,223 --> 00:00:16,766
<i>Why won't you leave us alone?!</i>

9
00:00:16,850 --> 00:00:19,936
<i>My son had nothing</i>
<i>to do with your friend's death!</i>

10
00:00:20,020 --> 00:00:22,731
<i>The night Louisa was murdered,</i>
<i>I was with Michelle.</i>

11
00:00:22,814 --> 00:00:25,608
<i>I just bumped into her, so we hooked up.</i>

12
00:00:25,692 --> 00:00:27,485
<i>When we asked you about Louisa,</i>

13
00:00:27,569 --> 00:00:28,945
<i>why didn't you tell us about Kyle?</i>

14
00:00:29,029 --> 00:00:30,613
<i>Did you ask about Kyle?</i>

15
00:00:30,697 --> 00:00:33,033
<i>You only asked about Louisa.</i>

16
00:00:33,116 --> 00:00:35,994
<i>We ran out of cooking oil. Go buy some.</i>

17
00:00:36,077 --> 00:00:39,164
<i>I don't want to go to the store at night!</i>

18
00:00:39,247 --> 00:00:40,790
<i>It's so dark outside!</i>

19
00:00:40,874 --> 00:00:42,333
<i>I'm scared!</i>

20
00:00:42,417 --> 00:00:46,254
- [grunt]
- [muffled scream]

21
00:00:47,547 --> 00:00:53,470
[sinister music playing]

22
00:01:04,522 --> 00:01:10,236
- [music becomes unsettling]
- [shovel digging]

23
00:01:12,280 --> 00:01:19,162
[theme music playing]

24
00:02:28,481 --> 00:02:29,566
Take it easy.

25
00:02:29,649 --> 00:02:32,110
[cicadas chirping]

26
00:02:32,193 --> 00:02:34,154
I don't think the photo was edited.

27
00:02:34,237 --> 00:02:36,197
I know when someone is lying.

28
00:02:37,031 --> 00:02:38,408
And Michelle definitely wasn't.

29
00:02:38,491 --> 00:02:40,410
I know you want to put Kyle in jail.

30
00:02:40,493 --> 00:02:42,162
I really want that bastard in jail!

31
00:02:43,580 --> 00:02:45,874
Then tell the PBI
that he's hiding here in Amurao.

32
00:02:46,291 --> 00:02:49,168
That'll teach him
that he can't run away with everything.

33
00:02:49,252 --> 00:02:51,671
So, we're back on square one.

34
00:02:53,339 --> 00:02:54,507
- [Lucas sighs heavily]
- [Erica sighs sharply]

35
00:02:54,591 --> 00:02:56,092
You know, we should just…

36
00:02:57,802 --> 00:03:00,263
We should just go home and take a break.

37
00:03:00,763 --> 00:03:01,764
Get some rest.

38
00:03:01,848 --> 00:03:04,267
What we should focus on is finding Edong.

39
00:03:04,350 --> 00:03:06,811
We keep running into dead ends.

40
00:03:08,646 --> 00:03:11,733
Lucas, you know how
your brother thinks. Maybe--

41
00:03:11,816 --> 00:03:14,068
He's no longer the brother Lucas knew!

42
00:03:14,986 --> 00:03:16,362
He's lost his sanity!

43
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:19,324
The police are already looking for Edong.

44
00:03:19,699 --> 00:03:21,826
We can focus on
solving Louisa's case for now.

45
00:03:22,952 --> 00:03:25,413
When will you give up on
the belief that Edong is the victim?

46
00:03:25,997 --> 00:03:28,166
He wasn't the victim
when he killed Celestino.

47
00:03:28,583 --> 00:03:31,419
Punishing you like this
doesn't make him the victim, either.

48
00:03:32,629 --> 00:03:34,589
What we have to do now is catch him

49
00:03:35,423 --> 00:03:37,800
and put an end
to his revenge plot against you,

50
00:03:39,135 --> 00:03:42,555
not run around in circles
trying to find Louisa's killer.

51
00:03:42,639 --> 00:03:43,681
Hang on.

52
00:03:44,724 --> 00:03:46,226
I thought you believed me.

53
00:03:46,309 --> 00:03:47,685
I believe you, Erica.

54
00:03:48,311 --> 00:03:49,312
But I'm sorry.

55
00:03:49,812 --> 00:03:52,357
He's not the killer
who's out to get you right now.

56
00:03:52,440 --> 00:03:53,316
It's Edong.

57
00:03:53,399 --> 00:03:57,195
So can we just worry about
Louisa's case after we catch Edong?

58
00:03:57,278 --> 00:03:59,656
I just want to do what's right.

59
00:03:59,739 --> 00:04:01,574
Your life is at stake here.

60
00:04:02,909 --> 00:04:05,453
It's no longer about
what's right and wrong.

61
00:04:06,704 --> 00:04:10,541
We need to catch Edong
before he gets the chance to hurt you.

62
00:04:10,625 --> 00:04:12,085
That's what matters to me now.

63
00:04:12,168 --> 00:04:16,005
[tense music playing]

64
00:04:16,089 --> 00:04:17,215
So, what?

65
00:04:18,299 --> 00:04:20,260
We're going to kill
him before he kills us?!

66
00:04:20,343 --> 00:04:21,886
If worse comes to worst, yes!

67
00:04:25,181 --> 00:04:27,684
If you're not ready
for that, I don't care.

68
00:04:28,434 --> 00:04:29,686
I'll kill if I have to.

69
00:04:33,773 --> 00:04:35,733
I'm not doing any of this
because I want to save Edong.

70
00:04:36,192 --> 00:04:37,193
I want to save you.

71
00:04:37,277 --> 00:04:39,821
[tense music continues]

72
00:04:39,904 --> 00:04:42,949
What do you think would
happen when you solve this case?

73
00:04:43,032 --> 00:04:45,952
You think Edong will say,
"Alright, we're good now"?

74
00:04:46,661 --> 00:04:48,579
He won't kill
you anymore because past is past?

75
00:04:49,455 --> 00:04:50,915
You said it yourself.

76
00:04:51,457 --> 00:04:53,918
Edong has completely lost his sanity.

77
00:04:54,002 --> 00:04:55,253
He's hopeless.

78
00:04:56,296 --> 00:04:57,839
I thought we both knew

79
00:04:57,922 --> 00:04:59,590
that we can't afford
to hold back when it comes to him.

80
00:05:02,093 --> 00:05:05,722
Because when he's done
terrorizing and torturing you,

81
00:05:06,431 --> 00:05:07,849
he will kill you.

82
00:05:09,267 --> 00:05:11,602
So, there are only 2
acceptable outcomes for him here.

83
00:05:13,563 --> 00:05:14,647
He goes to prison…

84
00:05:15,356 --> 00:05:16,441
or he dies.

85
00:05:16,524 --> 00:05:19,819
[tense music continues]

86
00:05:23,489 --> 00:05:25,074
[music fades]

87
00:05:25,158 --> 00:05:27,201
Like I said, let's just go home.

88
00:05:29,704 --> 00:05:30,663
[sighs sharply]

89
00:05:31,289 --> 00:05:33,499
- Erica--
- Geez, you're still yapping?

90
00:05:36,335 --> 00:05:37,837
- Hey.
- What?

91
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:41,257
If you really care about Erica,
you'll admit that I'm right.

92
00:05:41,340 --> 00:05:45,595
[tense music resumes]

93
00:05:49,265 --> 00:05:50,725
[music fades]

94
00:05:50,808 --> 00:05:52,060
Ma!

95
00:05:53,352 --> 00:05:54,896
- What?
- [boy panting]

96
00:05:54,979 --> 00:05:57,899
Ma, Katkat wasn't at the store.

97
00:05:57,982 --> 00:06:00,818
Miss Lina said she didn't go there.

98
00:06:00,902 --> 00:06:04,030
What? Where could she have gone to?

99
00:06:04,822 --> 00:06:06,115
Let's find her.

100
00:06:06,199 --> 00:06:11,037
[foreboding music plays, fades]

101
00:06:19,170 --> 00:06:20,338
Marco's right.

102
00:06:22,298 --> 00:06:23,841
I'm getting too hopeful.

103
00:06:25,510 --> 00:06:28,429
I didn't know
you wanted to save Edong that much.

104
00:06:29,555 --> 00:06:31,265
[sighs] You know my story.

105
00:06:32,642 --> 00:06:36,104
As a child,
my mother treated me like garbage.

106
00:06:36,979 --> 00:06:40,108
She punished me for
what my father did to her.

107
00:06:40,441 --> 00:06:43,903
I told myself I'd never do that to anyone.

108
00:06:45,488 --> 00:06:46,697
But I did.

109
00:06:48,741 --> 00:06:49,700
To Edong.

110
00:06:50,910 --> 00:06:53,162
It was so hard for me to accept that.

111
00:06:53,746 --> 00:06:55,915
Beth said I was angry with her.

112
00:06:56,332 --> 00:06:57,792
That's not true.

113
00:06:57,875 --> 00:07:00,086
The truth is, I'm angry at myself.

114
00:07:02,004 --> 00:07:04,799
[sighs] It's been
weighing on me for so long.

115
00:07:06,592 --> 00:07:08,094
I can't let it go.

116
00:07:10,596 --> 00:07:11,764
Erica.

117
00:07:14,267 --> 00:07:15,351
I'm sorry.

118
00:07:15,435 --> 00:07:17,687
[melancholic music playing]

119
00:07:17,770 --> 00:07:22,108
For all the times I accused you…

120
00:07:23,609 --> 00:07:24,986
of having no conscience.

121
00:07:26,529 --> 00:07:27,655
I admit,

122
00:07:28,322 --> 00:07:30,366
I still want to save my brother.

123
00:07:32,285 --> 00:07:33,703
I don't want him to die.

124
00:07:34,454 --> 00:07:36,581
But if anything happened to you,

125
00:07:38,416 --> 00:07:39,792
I wouldn't be able to bear it.

126
00:07:39,876 --> 00:07:45,298
[melancholic music continues]]

127
00:07:54,223 --> 00:07:56,434
[sobs softly]

128
00:08:06,027 --> 00:08:06,986
[Alice] Mel?

129
00:08:08,196 --> 00:08:09,447
Are you okay?

130
00:08:13,659 --> 00:08:19,665
[melancholic music continues]

131
00:08:41,187 --> 00:08:44,524
[interviewer] What do
you think of Mel Montenegro's scandal?

132
00:08:45,191 --> 00:08:47,818
- You know, Mel and I are good friends.
- [music fades]

133
00:08:47,902 --> 00:08:50,321
And we've worked together many times.

134
00:08:50,404 --> 00:08:54,075
<i>So, whatever the truth is,</i>
<i>it will eventually come out.</i>

135
00:08:54,158 --> 00:08:57,745
<i>But honestly,</i>
<i>I am here for her. I believe her…</i>

136
00:08:57,828 --> 00:09:00,790
[Tim] <i>She's not</i>
<i>the only one who'll show support.</i>

137
00:09:00,873 --> 00:09:03,751
We've talked to Dimples Romana,

138
00:09:03,834 --> 00:09:07,296
Kaila, Sue, Janella, and Charlie.

139
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:10,758
All of them will come
forward to support you, girl.

140
00:09:10,841 --> 00:09:12,802
And girl, get this!

141
00:09:12,885 --> 00:09:17,139
It's Jennica Sola!
Exclusive feature interview with you!

142
00:09:17,223 --> 00:09:18,724
<i>Wild, right?!</i>

143
00:09:18,808 --> 00:09:24,230
[melancholic music resumes]

144
00:09:24,313 --> 00:09:25,648
Just crickets?

145
00:09:26,983 --> 00:09:30,278
[Tim] <i>Mel? Hello? Are you still there?</i>

146
00:09:31,654 --> 00:09:33,072
It must've been disconnected.

147
00:09:34,782 --> 00:09:36,576
No, the call is still ongoing.

148
00:09:36,659 --> 00:09:38,536
[Tom] <i>Mel, did you hear us?</i>

149
00:09:39,579 --> 00:09:41,122
<i>This is the Jennica Sola, okay?</i>

150
00:09:41,205 --> 00:09:44,875
The one who exposed
the flood control issue publicly.

151
00:09:44,959 --> 00:09:49,672
Her team told us Anton
tried to get her on his side.

152
00:09:49,755 --> 00:09:51,549
But she's Team Mel.

153
00:09:51,632 --> 00:09:56,262
[melancholic music continues]

154
00:09:57,221 --> 00:09:58,264
Girl?

155
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:00,266
You with us?

156
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:02,184
[Tim] <i>Girl?</i>

157
00:10:02,893 --> 00:10:03,936
<i>- Girl!</i>
- [music fades]

158
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:05,187
Uh…

159
00:10:06,897 --> 00:10:08,107
When's the interview?

160
00:10:08,774 --> 00:10:11,611
Um… Actually, that's the thing.

161
00:10:11,694 --> 00:10:13,571
Uh… It's today.

162
00:10:13,988 --> 00:10:15,281
<i>Later this afternoon.</i>

163
00:10:15,364 --> 00:10:16,449
Today?

164
00:10:16,532 --> 00:10:18,868
[Tim] <i>We tried to get another date,</i>

165
00:10:18,951 --> 00:10:20,953
<i>but today's her only free time.</i>

166
00:10:21,037 --> 00:10:25,041
<i>She's flying to Cebu</i>
<i>to cover the recent earthquake tonight.</i>

167
00:10:25,124 --> 00:10:28,044
<i>Apparently,</i>
<i>they'll be there for a few days.</i>

168
00:10:28,127 --> 00:10:30,296
She's booked and busy.

169
00:10:30,713 --> 00:10:34,342
This is the best and
only time for us to do this interview.

170
00:10:35,009 --> 00:10:36,844
That's why we booked
her as soon as we could.

171
00:10:36,927 --> 00:10:39,597
We set the venue at your mom's hotel

172
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:41,307
<i>so you'd be comfortable.</i>

173
00:10:41,390 --> 00:10:43,059
[Tim] <i>We'll take care of everything.</i>

174
00:10:43,142 --> 00:10:45,436
<i>Just make sure you get there on time.</i>

175
00:10:46,228 --> 00:10:47,313
Yeah, okay.

176
00:10:47,897 --> 00:10:48,939
I'll see you.

177
00:10:49,482 --> 00:10:50,483
[Tim] <i>See you!</i>

178
00:10:50,566 --> 00:10:56,405
[pensive music playing]

179
00:11:10,878 --> 00:11:11,879
[Alice] Hey.

180
00:11:15,758 --> 00:11:16,801
Uh…

181
00:11:17,802 --> 00:11:19,845
I need to go back to Manila.

182
00:11:19,929 --> 00:11:22,681
Uh, I have an interview this afternoon.

183
00:11:26,685 --> 00:11:29,397
Worried about the interview?

184
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:33,150
[pensive music continues]

185
00:11:34,610 --> 00:11:35,820
About him then?

186
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:39,365
Lucas.

187
00:11:42,326 --> 00:11:44,120
Don't try to deny it.

188
00:11:45,246 --> 00:11:48,124
Have you told him how you feel about him?

189
00:11:51,919 --> 00:11:53,087
I'm scared.

190
00:11:57,675 --> 00:12:00,678
I'm afraid
that I might not like what he'll say.

191
00:12:01,512 --> 00:12:03,389
That he might say that…

192
00:12:05,349 --> 00:12:06,308
it's really over.

193
00:12:06,392 --> 00:12:10,980
[pensive music continues]

194
00:12:11,063 --> 00:12:12,773
[sobs]

195
00:12:19,655 --> 00:12:21,449
[Alice exhales heavily]

196
00:12:21,532 --> 00:12:23,492
And if so…

197
00:12:25,578 --> 00:12:26,495
what then?

198
00:12:32,501 --> 00:12:34,170
[music fades]

199
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:40,634
They need me in Manila.

200
00:12:47,141 --> 00:12:49,727
What happened? Is she okay?

201
00:12:54,815 --> 00:12:55,858
[sighs sharply]

202
00:12:57,193 --> 00:12:58,277
Erica,

203
00:12:59,278 --> 00:13:02,656
if there's something
going on between you and Lucas,

204
00:13:02,740 --> 00:13:04,116
you have to tell Mel.

205
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:05,784
[uneasy music playing]

206
00:13:05,868 --> 00:13:07,286
Nothing's going on between--

207
00:13:07,369 --> 00:13:09,205
Erica, she saw you.

208
00:13:09,288 --> 00:13:11,373
Mel saw you two last night.

209
00:13:11,457 --> 00:13:12,791
You and Lucas.

210
00:13:12,875 --> 00:13:14,543
Alice, we just talked.

211
00:13:14,627 --> 00:13:16,045
[Alice] Oh, come on, Erica.

212
00:13:16,504 --> 00:13:18,589
The way you two are when you're together,

213
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:21,008
it's not nothing.

214
00:13:21,634 --> 00:13:23,052
We both know it.

215
00:13:23,552 --> 00:13:26,305
We've already had
this conversation before.

216
00:13:29,642 --> 00:13:30,601
[Marco] Erica.

217
00:13:33,103 --> 00:13:36,815
[uneasy music continues, fades]

218
00:13:36,899 --> 00:13:39,360
Sorry for what happened last night.

219
00:13:41,779 --> 00:13:43,322
I shouldn't have snapped at you.

220
00:13:45,783 --> 00:13:48,035
But you're not going
to take back what you said?

221
00:13:49,745 --> 00:13:51,372
[sighs heavily] Nope.

222
00:13:52,248 --> 00:13:53,582
That's still what I think is right.

223
00:13:54,833 --> 00:13:57,211
If that's what
you want to do, then go ahead.

224
00:13:58,254 --> 00:14:00,297
But I'll still continue
to work on Louisa's case.

225
00:14:00,381 --> 00:14:01,423
[Marco sighs]

226
00:14:12,434 --> 00:14:13,477
Do you…

227
00:14:14,645 --> 00:14:15,854
still have feelings for him?

228
00:14:15,938 --> 00:14:21,318
[gentle music playing]

229
00:14:21,402 --> 00:14:22,570
What?

230
00:14:22,653 --> 00:14:23,696
For Lucas.

231
00:14:25,990 --> 00:14:27,825
I know you've said this before.

232
00:14:28,701 --> 00:14:30,244
You don't want a relationship because…

233
00:14:30,995 --> 00:14:32,580
you don't want things to get complicated.

234
00:14:33,372 --> 00:14:35,583
So you'd prefer
that nothing changes between us.

235
00:14:37,126 --> 00:14:38,627
I tried to understand that.

236
00:14:40,296 --> 00:14:42,256
But every time I see you together…

237
00:14:42,339 --> 00:14:47,052
[gentle music continues]

238
00:14:47,136 --> 00:14:50,514
Things are different now.

239
00:14:52,850 --> 00:14:54,310
Whatever you had back then…

240
00:14:55,644 --> 00:14:56,979
- is over.
- [music fades]

241
00:14:57,062 --> 00:14:59,690
We're looking for two
killers right now, Marco.

242
00:14:59,773 --> 00:15:02,818
Do you think I have time
to consider any romantic feelings?

243
00:15:03,736 --> 00:15:04,904
I don't get it.

244
00:15:04,987 --> 00:15:08,616
People always think
women are ruled by their emotions.

245
00:15:08,699 --> 00:15:10,492
That men are always our problem.

246
00:15:10,576 --> 00:15:13,370
Like women can't function without men.

247
00:15:13,454 --> 00:15:15,414
[sullen music playing]

248
00:15:15,497 --> 00:15:18,626
This is exactly why
I don't get into relationships.

249
00:15:18,709 --> 00:15:20,586
It's too complicated.

250
00:15:21,003 --> 00:15:23,672
And everyone has so
many assumptions about us.

251
00:15:26,842 --> 00:15:27,801
[huffs]

252
00:15:31,096 --> 00:15:32,848
[music fades]

253
00:15:34,391 --> 00:15:37,061
[Annette] <i>Where on earth is Edward?</i>
<i>It's already morning!</i>

254
00:15:37,478 --> 00:15:39,104
Look, I'm here.

255
00:15:39,605 --> 00:15:40,814
You need to calm down.

256
00:15:41,273 --> 00:15:44,026
<i>What if Althea really</i>
<i>did see Edong yesterday?</i>

257
00:15:44,109 --> 00:15:47,863
I'd never forgive myself
if something happened to her.

258
00:15:48,614 --> 00:15:50,699
I should've dropped
by like I was meant to.

259
00:15:50,783 --> 00:15:53,577
Then I'd have
to worry about the both of you.

260
00:15:54,161 --> 00:15:58,958
You know how
your migraine attacks affect you.

261
00:15:59,041 --> 00:16:01,168
Listen to me. Nothing happened here.

262
00:16:03,003 --> 00:16:04,004
[screen door opens]

263
00:16:05,422 --> 00:16:07,383
Oh, Uncle Edward is here.

264
00:16:07,841 --> 00:16:08,968
I heard that!

265
00:16:09,551 --> 00:16:11,387
Let me talk to him. Give him the phone.

266
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:12,513
Annette…

267
00:16:15,140 --> 00:16:17,393
Mama, you need to calm down.

268
00:16:17,476 --> 00:16:19,478
I told you, I'm okay.

269
00:16:19,561 --> 00:16:21,480
I still need to speak with him!

270
00:16:22,147 --> 00:16:23,565
Okay, I'll put you on speaker.

271
00:16:23,649 --> 00:16:24,525
Mama, please.

272
00:16:25,651 --> 00:16:26,527
[phone thuds]

273
00:16:26,610 --> 00:16:28,278
[uneasy music playing]

274
00:16:28,362 --> 00:16:29,405
Uncle.

275
00:16:30,155 --> 00:16:31,031
Althea.

276
00:16:31,907 --> 00:16:32,783
Frank.

277
00:16:34,702 --> 00:16:38,414
I'm sorry, I only got home this morning.

278
00:16:39,331 --> 00:16:40,207
[Annette] <i>Edward.</i>

279
00:16:40,290 --> 00:16:42,167
Something happened there yesterday!

280
00:16:42,251 --> 00:16:44,378
[uneasy music continues]

281
00:16:44,461 --> 00:16:46,422
What happened? Are you alright?

282
00:16:46,505 --> 00:16:47,756
- Tell me.
- Yes, uh…

283
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:49,967
Your Aunt Christina, how is she?

284
00:16:50,050 --> 00:16:51,135
- Oh, Mama…
- Love?

285
00:16:51,218 --> 00:16:54,722
Althea will explain
everything to you, Edward.

286
00:16:56,056 --> 00:16:57,307
It was nothing serious, Uncle.

287
00:16:57,391 --> 00:17:00,102
Sorry, Mama's just overreacting.

288
00:17:00,185 --> 00:17:01,979
<i>Everything's fine.</i>

289
00:17:02,312 --> 00:17:05,232
I thought I had seen Edong here.

290
00:17:05,983 --> 00:17:08,110
But I must've just imagined it.

291
00:17:09,486 --> 00:17:10,988
[ominous music sting]

292
00:17:11,071 --> 00:17:12,448
<i>He's here!</i>

293
00:17:12,531 --> 00:17:13,866
<i>Edong's here!</i>

294
00:17:13,949 --> 00:17:16,827
<i>At the back! Please, hurry!</i>

295
00:17:16,910 --> 00:17:17,953
<i>Aunt…</i>

296
00:17:18,037 --> 00:17:19,580
<i>He's right there! Quickly!</i>

297
00:17:20,247 --> 00:17:21,707
<i>Aunt Christina…</i>

298
00:17:23,834 --> 00:17:26,336
[Althea breathing nervously]

299
00:17:26,837 --> 00:17:29,465
The cops already checked the whole house

300
00:17:29,548 --> 00:17:31,633
and made sure he wasn't here.

301
00:17:32,342 --> 00:17:36,055
But… I think I ended up scaring Auntie.

302
00:17:37,014 --> 00:17:38,390
I'm sorry.

303
00:17:38,807 --> 00:17:42,770
<i>What did I tell you, Althea?</i>
<i>You shouldn't have gone there so soon.</i>

304
00:17:43,645 --> 00:17:45,355
<i>Edward, I was about to call you,</i>

305
00:17:45,439 --> 00:17:48,025
but Althea stopped me.

306
00:17:48,108 --> 00:17:51,111
Mama, I told you I'm okay.
Nothing to worry about.

307
00:17:51,195 --> 00:17:52,946
I just freaked out a little.

308
00:17:53,447 --> 00:17:54,448
[exhales softly]

309
00:17:55,699 --> 00:17:57,242
I'm really sorry.

310
00:17:57,868 --> 00:18:01,121
I just couldn't refuse
the folks at the donation drive.

311
00:18:03,207 --> 00:18:04,875
I lost track of time.

312
00:18:06,251 --> 00:18:07,628
It was evening before I knew it.

313
00:18:07,711 --> 00:18:10,839
[sighs] I was
supposed to head straight home.

314
00:18:10,923 --> 00:18:14,009
<i>But I was just too exhausted</i>

315
00:18:14,093 --> 00:18:15,677
and ended up sleeping in the van.

316
00:18:17,805 --> 00:18:21,558
[Althea]<i> Mama,</i>
<i>you heard how badly all of Santa Fe</i>

317
00:18:21,642 --> 00:18:23,936
<i>was affected by the recent storm?</i>

318
00:18:24,645 --> 00:18:28,232
The people have been trapped
with nothing to eat for three weeks now.

319
00:18:28,315 --> 00:18:32,444
To make matters worse,
the governor is absent.

320
00:18:32,528 --> 00:18:35,447
Turns out they're on
a family vacation in Japan.

321
00:18:35,531 --> 00:18:38,826
<i>So, Mama, I understand why Uncle Edward</i>

322
00:18:38,909 --> 00:18:40,452
wants to help.

323
00:18:41,161 --> 00:18:43,122
[Frank] I hope
that clears things up, Annette.

324
00:18:43,539 --> 00:18:45,415
<i>Why can't those</i>

325
00:18:45,499 --> 00:18:48,001
useless politicians do their damn job?

326
00:18:48,085 --> 00:18:51,463
[exhales sharply]
Annette, I'm really sorry.

327
00:18:51,547 --> 00:18:52,673
Frank.

328
00:18:55,384 --> 00:18:56,385
[Frank] Watch your step.

329
00:18:56,885 --> 00:18:58,637
[Althea] Papa, did you text Mama yet?

330
00:18:58,720 --> 00:19:01,140
Yes. And she's been
asking for updates nonstop.

331
00:19:01,223 --> 00:19:03,809
Pa, please let me come here again.

332
00:19:03,892 --> 00:19:05,644
You should be asking your mom.

333
00:19:05,727 --> 00:19:06,728
- Good morning.
- [gate creaks]

334
00:19:06,812 --> 00:19:08,230
[engine starts]

335
00:19:08,313 --> 00:19:11,233
[low rumbling]

336
00:19:11,316 --> 00:19:14,945
[Frank grunts] Boss,
drive us there. Just go head straight.

337
00:19:17,906 --> 00:19:23,912
[foreboding music playing]

338
00:19:28,876 --> 00:19:33,672
[music becomes unsettling]

339
00:19:35,465 --> 00:19:37,926
[woman] <i>Any news about Katkat?</i>

340
00:19:38,010 --> 00:19:39,553
<i>Please, help us!</i>

341
00:19:39,970 --> 00:19:41,680
<i>I'm begging you!</i>

342
00:19:42,097 --> 00:19:43,557
<i>Jerry? Kaloy?</i>

343
00:19:43,640 --> 00:19:46,393
<i>I shouldn't have told</i>
<i>her to go out last night.</i>

344
00:19:46,476 --> 00:19:50,939
[unsettling music continues]

345
00:19:56,945 --> 00:19:57,988
[soft thud]

346
00:19:58,655 --> 00:20:02,409
[soil crunching]

347
00:20:04,453 --> 00:20:05,454
[shovel thuds]

348
00:20:05,996 --> 00:20:07,331
[man panting]

349
00:20:12,794 --> 00:20:18,175
[unsettling music continues]

350
00:20:31,521 --> 00:20:37,319
[music becomes sinister]

351
00:20:39,738 --> 00:20:40,822
[body thuds]

352
00:20:40,906 --> 00:20:45,077
[sinister music continues]

353
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:46,328
[ominous music sting]

354
00:20:46,411 --> 00:20:47,496
[Edong] What are you?

355
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:53,335
<i>You cunning demon.</i>

356
00:20:54,419 --> 00:20:55,837
[low chuckle]

357
00:20:57,589 --> 00:20:59,675
<i>You've been there all along.</i>

358
00:21:00,259 --> 00:21:02,844
<i>Deceiving everyone</i>
<i>into thinking you're normal,</i>

359
00:21:03,804 --> 00:21:04,972
<i>safe to be around.</i>

360
00:21:05,973 --> 00:21:10,310
<i>But no one truly escapes you, do they?</i>

361
00:21:10,727 --> 00:21:12,938
[Edong laughs mockingly]

362
00:21:14,314 --> 00:21:16,858
[Edward moaning softly]

363
00:21:18,318 --> 00:21:19,403
[shovel thuds]

364
00:21:20,320 --> 00:21:23,699
[Edong] You won't
stop me from getting to Alice.

365
00:21:24,825 --> 00:21:26,660
Or Mel.

366
00:21:27,661 --> 00:21:29,371
Or Beth.

367
00:21:31,164 --> 00:21:32,666
Or Erica.

368
00:21:33,083 --> 00:21:34,126
[Edward grunts]

369
00:21:34,209 --> 00:21:35,961
[Edong] Any of them.

370
00:21:37,296 --> 00:21:38,422
[soil crunches]

371
00:21:38,505 --> 00:21:43,719
[unsettling music intensifies]

372
00:21:43,802 --> 00:21:47,097
I will stand on top of your dead body

373
00:21:47,764 --> 00:21:50,309
if that's what it takes to get to them.

374
00:21:51,476 --> 00:21:53,478
[chuckling maliciously]

375
00:21:53,562 --> 00:21:58,608
[dramatic music playing]

376
00:22:02,696 --> 00:22:05,157
[woman] <i>I shouldn't have</i>
<i>told her to go out last night.</i>

377
00:22:06,074 --> 00:22:08,910
<i>I even got mad when she refused.</i>

378
00:22:08,994 --> 00:22:10,912
<i>Now she's missing.</i>

379
00:22:10,996 --> 00:22:12,998
[watchman] <i>We'd better</i>
<i>report this to the police station.</i>

380
00:22:13,081 --> 00:22:14,041
[woman sobs]<i> Yes.</i>

381
00:22:14,124 --> 00:22:19,463
[dramatic music continues]

382
00:22:24,843 --> 00:22:27,888
[Anton] <i>I'm being held accountable</i>
<i>for something that I didn't even do.</i>

383
00:22:27,971 --> 00:22:30,348
<i>Anyone who is innocent…</i>
<i>if you do them an injustice,</i>

384
00:22:30,432 --> 00:22:32,476
<i>and they would really go crazy.</i>

385
00:22:32,559 --> 00:22:35,103
<i>- So, it's not Kyle.</i>
<i>- This keeps happening to us.</i>

386
00:22:35,187 --> 00:22:37,105
<i>Don't tell me</i>
<i>you still think it was Edong.</i>

387
00:22:37,189 --> 00:22:38,482
<i>Well, you can't blame me.</i>

388
00:22:38,565 --> 00:22:42,069
<i>We keep going around in circles,</i>
<i>and it always leads us back to Edong.</i>

389
00:22:42,152 --> 00:22:43,028
<i>I can't.</i>

390
00:22:43,111 --> 00:22:45,530
<i>It's protecting you from something</i>
<i>you're not ready to deal with.</i>

391
00:22:45,614 --> 00:22:47,699
<i>I've been traumatized</i>
<i>and devastated enough.</i>

392
00:22:47,783 --> 00:22:51,161
<i>What else is there to know</i>
<i>that could devastate me even more?</i>
